cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper belongs to the computer science sub-category of security and privacy (cs.CR) as it discusses the privacy and anonymity features of Tor hidden services and the potential for shady services to operate on the platform. It also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) as it analyses the open ports of the hidden services. The paper also involves data structures (cs.DS) as it collects and analyses a large dataset of hidden service descriptors. Additionally, it involves social and information networks (cs.SI) as it looks at the popularity of hidden services. Finally, it involves cybercrime (cs.CY) as it identifies botnets as the most popular type of hidden service.
